Question.Text: A 20-Year-Old Woman from the Democratic Republic of the Congo With a history of fever, malaise, headache, dry cough, swelling of the neck and a disseminated skin rash, which appeared 2 days after the symptoms began. The symptoms is also accompanied by a disseminated uniform vesiculopustular skin rash including the palms and soles of the feet as well as the oral mucosa and a prominent cervical lymphadenopathy.
